The paper focuses on applying a novel optimization scheme from image processing and machine learning to achieve controllable and realistic fluid simulations. This suggests that the paper may belong to the computer graphics (cs.GR) or computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of acceleration schemes tailored to specific problems, which could fall under the computational engineering (cs.CE) or numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also discusses the use of level-of-detail adjustment and resimulation with different fluid parameters, which could fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
